      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's what i thought... it feels way more intentional than just \"personalized experiences\" though. like, it's not just about playing music i like, it's like the house knows exactly when i'm getting agitated before i even realize it. it's almost like they are running some kind of live testing on my reactions. do u think there's a way they'd actually flag someone if their emotional response doesn't fit a certain profile?",
